description: A black basalt obelisk is imbedded in the hilltop and stands like a shadow against the night sky.  Just to the north, at the very crest of the hill, rises a circular tower of granite blocks.  A scraggly hawthorn tree grows out from a ledge to the south, clinging with spindly roots to an outthrust stone.

A black basalt obelisk is imbedded in the hilltop and stands out starkly against the pale sky.  Just to the north, at the very crest of the hill, rises a circular tower of granite blocks.  A scraggly hawthorn tree grows out from a ledge to the south, clinging with spindly roots to an outthrust stone.
title: [Tower Hill, South Obelisk]
